findings.lower_chest: Mild dependent atelectasis bilaterally, no pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdomen.hepatobiliary: Liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation, no focal lesions, no biliary dilatation, gallbladder normal.
abdomen.pancreas: Normal attenuation, no focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation, no peripancreatic stranding.
abdomen.spleen: Normal size and attenuation, no focal lesions.
abdomen.urinary: Kidneys normal and symmetric in size with normal nephrogram, no focal lesions or hydronephrosis, no perinephric abnormality.
abdomen.gastrointestinal: Stomach unremarkable, small bowel normal, colon and rectum normal, appendix measures up to 8 mm with no surrounding fat stranding, no pneumoperitoneum or fluid collection.
abdomen.pelvis: Urinary bladder and distal ureters unremarkable, no free fluid in pelvis.
abdomen.reproductive_organs: 3.6 x 2.6 x 3.5 cm ovoid hyperdense right uterine structure with a surrounding halo of hypodensity and thin curvilinear hyperdensities at the periphery.
abdomen.lymph_nodes: No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, no pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy.
abdomen.bones: No worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
abdomen.soft_tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall within normal limits.
